  "abstract": "Three sorghum cytoplasmic male sterile lines CSV4 A(V), CSV4 A(G1) and CSV4 A(M), grouped as A4, were\r\ncompared with amilo (A1) and two other non-milo (A2 andA3) cytoplasms for their RFLP patterns ofmitochondrial\r\nDNA (mtDNA). A 9.7 kb clone from pearl millet mtDNA discriminated each of the three A4 entries whereas other\r\nmaize and pearl millet mtDNA clones used could not distinguish this group completely. The molecular differences\r\nwithin the A4 cytoplasmic group offer some explanation for the inconsistency in the fertility restoration behaviour\r\nof these A4 lines obtained with a definite set of testers in the field.",
